  <title translate="true">Tip #36</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Minor updates to Dolphin are made available as patch files which can be automatically downloaded by the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Live Update</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> facility. &#160;As each patch file is installed your image will be brought up to a particular patch level. &#160;.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">You can tell the current patch level of your system from the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Help/About Dolphin Smalltalk</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> screen.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
